The lammergeier ……. …… the lammergeier ……. It kills wild bulls in the foothills, and it kills the stags in the high mountains.

@(43-45=c4143.A.43) Raven, raven, your eggs are shining bright! Raven bird, your eggs are shining bright! Where do people carry off your holy eggs, your …… eggs to?

@(46-48=c4143.A.46) The ostrich …… her eggs on the hillside. She receives those eggs as something to carry: the bird knows how to keep watch at night.

@(49-53=c4143.A.49) The peacock spends the day keeping watch. The holy bird, the peacock, spends the day calling '@fsux{ḫaya}'. A bird red from cornelian, blue from lapis lazuli, white (?) from chalcedony (?), with all kinds of gold, and leather inlaid with gold -- may the coppersmith fashion the peacock for you thus.

